 Two traffic officers and one police officer from Middelburg have been arrested on charges of corruption and are currently being questioned at the Middelburg Police Station. The crackdown, which has been named operation take down, took off this morning in Nelspruit, where the Hawks and DPCI targeted areas in the Mpumalanga region. Also read: Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation Captain Dineo Sekgotodi, the media spokesperson behind the operation, has informed that one police officer and two traffic officers were allegedly arrested this morning in Komatipoort. Lucky Mabena, Khethiwe Mkhabela and David Mahlare Ntuli have appeared in the Komatipoort Magistrate’s Court, facing charges of corruption and fraud for soliciting bribes from motorists along the N4, targeting foreign nationals in particular. The names of the other suspects cannot be released until they have appeared in court.      Four killed after minibus and truck collide on N11 near Doornkop Elderly lady escapes with her life Parkrun fever breaks out Military troop imposter arrested • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za